 (Apr. 12, EF2)}}\n|03:45\u201303:50\n|{{convert|3.04|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A tornado touched down just outside downtown Cleveland and soon impacted a residential area where it injured six people; 26 homes were destroyed, 23 suffered major damage, and 62 had minor damage. A church also sustained heavy damage.\n|<ref name=\"MRX_0412\">{{cite web |agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Morristown, Tennessee |title=NWS Damage Survey for 04/12/2020 Tornado Event Update #1|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSMRX&e=202004161807|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet |date=April 16, 2020 |accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|E of [[Cleveland, Tennessee|Cleveland]]\n|[[Bradley County, Tennessee|Bradley]]\n|[[Tennessee|TN]]\n|{{Coord|35.1663|-84.8242|name=Cleveland (Apr. 12, EF1)}}\n|03:50\u201303:55\n|{{convert|5.09|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n| Several homes sustained significant roof damage and barns were destroyed. Hundreds of trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref name=\"MRX_0412\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|E of [[Tasso, Tennessee|Tasso]]\n|[[Bradley County, Tennessee|Bradley]], [[Polk County, Tennessee|Polk]]\n|[[Tennessee|TN]]\n|{{Coord|35.2046|-84.7751|name=Tasso (Apr. 12, EF1)}}\n|03:55\u201304:00\n|{{convert|4.91|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Hundreds of trees were snapped or uprooted and a few homes sustained minor damage.\n|<ref name=\"MRX_0412\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n===April 13 event===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|+ List of confirmed tornadoes \u2013 Monday, April 13, 2020{{efn|All dates are based on the local [[time zone]] where the tornado touched down; however, all times are in [[Coordinated Universal Time]] for consistency.|group=note|name=Date/Time}}\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:3%; text-al